---
title: Ricotta Ravioli with Blistered Tomatoes & Asparagus Basil Cream Sauce & Garlic Bread
description: We love ravioli for many reasons—chiefly, its pillowy luxuriousness and how quickly it helps you get a hearty dinner on the table. These tomato-ricotta ravioli make a perfect base for a ton of other great flavors: juicy blistered tomatoes, sautéed asparagus, and caramelized shallots in a creamy basil sauce, with fresh spinach wilted right in. On the side is toasted ciabatta garlic bread for a crisp, extra-savory boost to this 15-minute meal that tastes like you were cooking it all day.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65afe4dea33a91ae6a3f7dbd-8fed5c1e.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65afe4dea33a91ae6a3f7dbd.pdf
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Southern Europe
nutrition:
  calories: 840 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 20 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 25 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 1700 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/ricotta-ravioli-with-blistered-tomatoes-and-asparagus-65afe4dea33a91ae6a3f7dbd
---

Bring a #medium pot{} of water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @asparagus{6%ounce}; cut on a diagonal into 1-inch pieces. Thinly slice
@shallot{1}(thinly sliced). Quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a hot #large pan{}.
Add asparagus and @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}; season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until asparagus is browned and tomatoes
are blistered, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out
pan.

Once water is boiling, gently add @fresh tomato ricotta ravioli{9%ounce} to
#pot{}. Reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente
and floating to the top, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Reserve ¾ cup pasta cooking water, then drain. Gently shake #strainer{}
with ravioli in it to remove as much moisture as possible.

While ravioli cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over
medium heat. Add shallot and cook, stirring constantly, until softened,
~{30-60%seconds}.

Whisk in @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon},
@basil paste{20%g}, and ¼ cup plain water (½ cup for 4). Bring sauce to a boil
then add @spinach{5%ounce} (in batches if necessary) and stir to wilt,
~{30-60%seconds}.

> Spinach may add moisture to your sauce. Cook longer if you like a thicker sauce!

Add drained ravioli, blistered tomatoes and asparagus, and a squeeze of
lemon; toss until evenly coated in a creamy sauce. (If sauce is too thick,
add reserved pasta cooking water 1 TBSP at a time until desired consistency is
reached.) Season with salt and pepper.

Halve @ciabatta roll{1} and toast. Spread cut sides with as much
@garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon} as you like; halve on a diagonal.

Top ravioli with @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}. Serve with garlic bread and
any remaining lemon wedges on the side.